§8- The whole passage is very corrupt in the MSS.. but the corrections of Madvig have been generally received. His earlier suggestion of strepere for teneri has not been admitted into the text. The change of form from missi (sunt) to teneri is in itself awkward, the MSS. read et ubi... ue quis moram, to which Madvig objects that the terms of the edict would be general, and not addressed to the sailors individually‚ and he therefore corrects it to ne quid, which would explain the object of the foregoing direction. The et he changes to ut, but this seems questionable.
